#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_micro.md:1
#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_micro.md:4
msgid "Behringer CMD Micro"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_micro.md:10
msgid "Behringer CMD Micro (schematic view)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_micro.md:12
msgid ""
"The *Behringer CMD Micro* is a simple controller for basic two-channel "
"mixing. This device does not have a built in sound card, so it would require"
" a {ref}`splitter cable <hardware-splitter-cables>` or {ref}`separate audio "
"interface <hardware-audio-interfaces>` to be able to preview tracks in "
"headphones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_micro.md:16
msgid ""
"[Manufacturer’s product "
"page](https://www.behringer.com/en/products/0700-aai)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_micro.md:20
msgid "Mapping description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_micro.md:23
msgid ""
"**Cue**, **Play/Pause**, **Sync**, **Load A**, **Load B**, the **Level** / "
"**Browse** knobs, and the **crossfader** all behave as labeled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_micro.md:26
msgid "**Cue A** and **Cue B** send the respective track to the headphones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_micro.md:27
msgid "The inner vertical sliders control the track’s volume."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_micro.md:28
msgid "The outer sliders control the playback speed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_micro.md:29
msgid "The **1**, and **2** buttons toggle a 4 and 8 beat loop, respectively."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_micro.md:31
msgid ""
"The **Pitch Bend** buttons temporarily adjust the playback rate. They can be"
" configured to change the key of the track instead by setting the "
"``PitchBendsKey`` option to true at the top of the JS file (open the JS file"
" in a text editor such as Notepad, TextEdit, or gEdit to change this). With "
"the PitchBendsKey option, when both buttons are pressed simultaneously, the "
"key is reset to the track’s default key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_micro.md:38
msgid "Jog Wheels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/behringer_cmd_micro.md:41
msgid ""
"The jog wheels are touch enabled. When the top is pressed, they emulate "
"turntable scratching. When the side is touched, they affect the playback "
"speed (jog)."
msgstr ""
